com.i2group.apollo.externaldata.delpsservice

Interface IDelpsService


  • public interface IDelpsService
    A set of methods for interacting with an Intelligence Analysis Platform DELPS (data load ELP stage) solution, including the ability to synchronize Items in the ELP stage with changing data in an external source.
    Since:
    5.0

    • Method Detail

      • createOrReplaceItemsXml

        void createOrReplaceItemsXml(String dataSourceId,
                           byte[] xmlSource)
                             throws ValidationException,
                                    InvalidArgumentException,
                                    ElpStageUnavailableException
        Creates Items from the platform-compatible XML in the specified XmlPropertyValue, and then adds or replaces them in the item store of the specified ELP stage.

        If the identifier of a created Item matches the identifier of an Item that is already in the store, then the cards on the created Item replace the cards on the existing Item.

        Parameters:
        dataSourceId - A String that contains the identifier of the ELP stage to interact with.
        xmlSource - A byte array that contains platform-compatible XML.

        The XML in xmlSource must contain information for a consistent set of Items. That is, if the XML describes a link, then it must also describe the ends of that link.

        If the external data source supports multiple cards, then the XML in xmlSource must specify a unique identifier for each card. Otherwise, the XML can use the same identifier for both the item and the card.

        Throws:
        ValidationException - If the XML in xmlSource cannot be converted into Items.
        InvalidArgumentException - If the specified ELP stage does not exist.
        ElpStageUnavailableException - If the specified ELP stage fails to add or replace the Items.

      • createOrReplaceItems

        void createOrReplaceItems(String dataSourceId,
                        List<Item> items)
                          throws InvalidArgumentException,
                                 ElpStageUnavailableException
        Adds or replaces the specified Items in the item store of the specified ELP stage.

        If the identifier of an Item matches the identifier of an Item that is already in the store, then the cards on the created Item replace the cards on the existing Item.

        Parameters:
        dataSourceId - A String that contains the identifier of the ELP stage to interact with.
        items - A List of Items.

        The list does not need to be self-consistent, but it must be consistent with the state of the ELP stage item store. That is, if the list contains a link, then it does not need to contain the ends of that link, provided that they already exist in the item store.

        Throws:
        InvalidArgumentException - If the specified ELP stage does not exist.
        ElpStageUnavailableException - If the specified ELP stage fails to add or replace the Items.

      • deleteItems

        void deleteItems(String dataSourceId,
               List<String> itemKeys)
                 throws InvalidArgumentException,
                        ElpStageUnavailableException,
                        ItemNotFoundException
        Deletes the Items with ItemIdentifiers that contain the specified String keys from the item store of the specified ELP stage.
        Parameters:
        dataSourceId - A String that contains the identifier of the ELP stage to interact with.
        itemKeys - Strings containing the keys from the ItemIdentifiers of the Items to delete.
        Throws:
        InvalidArgumentException - If the specified ELP stage does not exist.
        ElpStageUnavailableException - If the specified ELP stage fails to delete the Items.
        ItemNotFoundException - If one of the Items is not found in the specified ELP stage.

        Purges the Items with ItemIdentifiers that contain the specified String keys from the item store of the specified ELP stage.

        ElpStageUnavailableException - If the specified ELP stage fails to purge the Items.
        ItemNotFoundException - If one of the Items is not found in the specified ELP stage.
